            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The spectra must first be corrected for the change in",
                "efficiency with c.m. beam energy.",
                "Errors on the resonance energies and( hence 22Mg",
                "excitation energies) result from the angular straggling",
                "of protons through the gas and detectors, the error in",
                "the energy loss corrected proton energy and the finite",
                "pixel size and the error in the resonance energy",
                "resulting from the Lorentzian fitting."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The Radioactive Ion Beam facility at the University",
                "Catholique de Louvain in Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium was",
                "used to carry out the experimental work.",
                "Two 200 mm**2 face barrier detectors, at 170-degree on",
                "either side of the beam line, were used to detect",
                "elastically scattered 18Ne beam particles from a",
                " 200 mug/cm**2 Au foil. This allowed the beam to be",
                "normalized."
              ]
            }
          ],
